extractValuesAndLabels

public static void extractValuesAndLabels(org.openrdf.query.TupleQueryResult res,
                                          java.util.Vector<java.util.Vector<java.lang.Number>> values,
                                          java.util.Vector<org.openrdf.model.Value> labels,
                                          java.lang.String input,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> outputs,
                                          ReadDataManager queryDM,
                                          boolean groupByDatasetVariable)
                                   throws org.openrdf.query.QueryEvaluationException
Extracts values and labels for the chart data model from a tuple query result iterator. The iterator is closed before returning. If groupByDatasetVariable is set to true the output names will be taken from dataset variable, the values and labels will be extracted from a re-aggregated two-dimensional query result. The list of outputs will be filled with the dataset names.

Parameters:
res - the query result iterator
values - initialized, empty vector to collect values
labels - initialized,empty vector to collect values
input -
queryDM -
outputs -
groupByDatasetVariable -
Throws:
org.openrdf.query.QueryEvaluationException
